cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to estimate the pose of a satellite, which is a problem in robotics and space engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves geometric optimization and nonlinear optimization, which are related to robotics and control systems, hence cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely category. The use of machine learning models for landmark regression suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible category. The paper also involves the use of a priori reconstructed 3D models, which is related to artificial intelligence and computer graphics, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with space proximity operations, which is related to aerospace engineering, hence cs.GR (Graphics) is another possible category.
